# AI Resume Screener — Project Context

Full-stack RAG chat: ask natural-language questions about CV PDFs → LangGraph agents retrieve grounded chunks → answer with source citations.

## Stack

| Layer | Tech |
|---|---|
| Frontend | Vite 6 · React 19 · TypeScript strict · Tailwind CSS v4 · shadcn/ui |
| Backend | FastAPI · LangGraph · Python 3.11+ |
| LLM | Google Gemini `gemini-2.0-flash` |
| Embeddings | Google `text-embedding-004` |
| Vector store | ChromaDB (local, persistent) |
| PDF extraction | pymupdf4llm |
| CV generation | Seed JSON · ReportLab · `scripts/generate_cvs.py` |

## Two LangGraph agents

```
ingest_agent:   extract_text → chunk_by_section → embed → store_chroma → verify_index
chat_agent:     retrieve → validate_context → generate_answer → cite_sources
```

CV PDFs are generated offline from `data/seed/profiles.json` — not via LangGraph.

## Key files

- `data/seed/profiles.json` — demo candidates
- `scripts/generate_cvs.py` — seed → PDF + manifest
- `backend/app/cv_renderer.py` — ReportLab PDF builder
- `backend/app/agents/ingest_agent.py` — offline RAG indexing
- `backend/app/agents/chat_agent.py` — runtime Q&A
- `backend/app/invariants.py` — runtime guards (`InvariantError`)
- `backend/app/schemas/` — Pydantic types (chat, cv, rag)
- `backend/app/api/routes/` — FastAPI routers
- `backend/app/rag/` — chunker, store, retriever
- `frontend/src/types/api.ts` — mirrors `schemas/chat.py` (camelCase)

## Docs

- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` — flows, data layout, API
- `docs/DEVELOPMENT.md` — commit workflow, local setup

## Constraints

- Chat must not hallucinate: `validate_context` blocks low-score retrieval.
- `check_sources_from_retrieved` — every citation maps to a real chunk.
- `data/chroma/` gitignored; `data/cvs/` committed for demo.
- Tests: `cd backend && pytest -v`
